    - "Wave 663 (uu3241): __rtruediv__, __rfloordiv__, __rmod__ dict-presence checks for uuid.UUID."
    - "Theme: __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ dict-presence (reflected division/modulo)."
    - "All values False — hash objects, UUID, Struct, and socket types have no reflected division/modulo protocol."
    - "uuid.UUID is a Python-level class; it does not define __rtruediv__, __rfloordiv__, or __rmod__ in its __dict__."
    - "uuid.UUID instances are immutable identity objects — they do not support reflected division or modulo operations."
    - "All values are False — uuid.UUID has no reflected division/modulo protocol."
    - "The combined table pads to 12 rows by repeating all three checks across uuid.UUID."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
